# Cursor Rules — APAP Living Resource

Always consult:
- docs/STEP_0_SPEC.md (data contract + label rules)
- docs/PRD.md (user stories, UX needs, scope)
- docs/CONTEXT_INDEX.md and context/ (historical reference)


How to use context/:
- Use context/ to understand the METRICS, cohort breakdowns, and narrative patterns we’ve used historically.
- Do NOT copy layouts from HTML working docs or spreadsheet tabs into the product UI.
- UI decisions must follow docs/PRD.md and user stories, not legacy working-doc structure.

Implementation priorities:
1) Correct ingest/join/rolling-window metrics and labels (deterministic)
2) Explainability (“why” bullets) for every label
3) Cohort breakdown tables and filters
4) APAP overview vs configurable goals
5) AI summary that only summarizes computed metrics provided as structured input

Guardrails:
- No LLM-driven calculations. All metrics/labels must be deterministic code.
- AI Summary must only reference numbers present in a generated metrics bundle.

Always consult docs/DESIGN_SPEC.md for layout/components/states before implementing UI.
UI must use src/styles/tokens.css variables for surfaces and semantic colors (no hard-coded colors).
Typography must follow the DESIGN_SPEC.md text ramp guidelines.

Reference CHANGELOG.md for context on previous development efforts.